config.text: Estonian Land Board 3D

Estonian Land Board 3D



Data


The map application models are based on elevation points from aerial laser scanning. The models are more detailed in densely populated areas and less detailed in sparsely populated areas.


  • Buildings - Nearly 800,000 buildings based on ETAK contours. By clicking on the buildings, you can access external databases. Buildings meet LOD2 level of detail.
  • Point clouds - point clouds of Tallinn, Tartu, Prnu and Kuressaare visualized based on classes.
  • Trees - as an example, the application shows realistic and analytical trees in Kuressaare and Tartu based on Esri technology. Click on the tree to see the height.
  • Elevation model
  • WMS basic data on cadastral boundaries and narrowings.


More precise info: Geo3D Data
